   Condition Center

Gout

Gout is a type of arthritis caused by a buildup of uric acid crystals in the
joints (particularly the big toe). Gout symptoms include warmth, pain,
swelling, redness, and extreme tenderness of the affected joints, as well as
chills and fever.

